&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Paediatric Orthopaedic and Trauma Surgeon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barts Health NHS Trust &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Paediatric Orthopaedic and Trauma Surgeon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time -10PAs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a Consultant Paediatric and Orthopaedic Surgeon based at The Royal London. You will be joining a Barts wide Paediatric Orthopaedic department with 4.5 consultant surgeons. The ideal appointment to this post will have dual roles. Firstly, to support the paediatric orthopaedic and trauma service at Barts Health and secondly, it is envisaged that the appointee will participate actively in the ongoing development of the paediatric frame service, from both trauma and limb deformity perspectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold full registration with the General Medical Council and preferably be on the Specialist Registrar, or equivalent. lnformal discussions are encouraged and you are invited to contact Ms Paulien Bijlsma (Paediatric Orthopaedic Lead) paulien.bijlsma@nhs.net or Ms Homa Arshad (Clinical Lead, Orthopaedics) homa.arshad@nhs.net;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively,please contact Ms Caitlin Bush,Service Manager via Email address:caitlin.bush@nhs.net and Telephone number:07491237975&lt;/p&gt;
